author: COMSOL
description: An RFID system consists of a reader antenna and a transponder tag. As the wavelength typically is much larger than system dimensions, the interaction between reader and transponder is well described by transformer action. A magnetostatic model is used to compute the mutual inductance between the reader and transponder.
